-- в”Ђв”Ђ TinaCMS в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$TinaCMS is an open-source, Git-backed headless CMS with live visual editing for React frameworks like Next.js, storing content as Markdown or MDX directly in a GitHub repository.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$freemium$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free (self-hosted); TinaCloud from $24/month$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2019, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$Neutral Bay, New South Wales, Australia$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$TinaCMS Review 2026: Pricing, Features and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$TinaCMS is a Git-backed headless CMS with live visual editing. Compare TinaCMS pricing plans, key features and how it stacks up against other CMS tools.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$TinaCMS is an open-source, Git-backed headless content management system built for developers using React-based frameworks such as Next.js and Gatsby. It was released publicly in October 2019 as the successor to Forestry.io, a closed-source Git-backed CMS that launched in 2016; the original Forestry.io team built TinaCMS to add real-time, inline visual editing on top of a similar Git-as-database architecture. In May 2024, Australian software consultancy SSW (Superior Software for Windows) acquired TinaCMS and now maintains and develops the product. TinaCMS's core differentiator is that content edits happen directly on the live rendered page rather than in a separate admin form, and every save is committed as a Git commit to the site's own GitHub repository, so content is stored as Markdown or MDX files alongside code rather than in a proprietary database. This makes it attractive to teams that want a CMS for static or JAMstack sites without giving up version control, branching, or the ability to self-host. TinaCMS operates a hybrid open-source-plus-SaaS model: the core editing framework is free and open source and can be self-hosted, while TinaCloud is the commercial, hosted layer that adds real-time collaboration, editorial workflows, role-based access and managed authentication. TinaCloud pricing starts with a free tier for two users, then scales through Team, around 24 US dollars per month, Team Plus, around 41 US dollars per month, and Business, around 249 US dollars per month, with custom Enterprise pricing for larger organizations needing SSO and dedicated support. TinaCMS competes with other Git-based and headless CMS options such as Contentful, Sanity, Decap CMS and Strapi, distinguishing itself through its emphasis on true inline visual editing rather than a separate content dashboard.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '10cff4ac-f281-4d9e-998a-dc5742fcfd08';

